Editing a Visual Program: The Basics #!N #!EC #!N #!N When 
you open the Visual Program Editor (VPE) with the dx -edit 
command, or by choosing  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   New Visual Program #!EF in the 
Startup window, you will see a large blank area (the "canvas") 
and two "palettes" to its left (see  #!Lvpwndw4,dxall6 f Figure 4  #!EL  ). The palette 
at top lists "categories" of tools (modules). The palette below it 
lists the tools in the currently selected (highlighted) category. #!N #!N 
